"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-08-02-paris-2024-olympics-riddled-controversy-missteps\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"To say that the Paris 2024 Olympics has been riddled with controversy and missteps would be an understatement.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 110, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 22, \"end\": 35, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"2024 Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"controversy\", \"from\": 58, \"to\": 69}, {\"ngram\": \"missteps\", \"from\": 74, \"to\": 82}, {\"ngram\": \"an understatement\", \"from\": 92, \"to\": 109}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The world's foremost sports competition, featuring more than 200 countries and 11,000 athletes, represented in 42 Olympic disciplines, officially kicked off last Friday (July 26) with what was promised by the organisers as an opening ceremony that would be \\\"bold, original, and unique\\\".\", \"from\": 111, \"to\": 397, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The world's foremost sports competition\", \"from\": 111, \"to\": 150}, {\"ngram\": \"more than 200 countries\", \"from\": 162, \"to\": 185}, {\"ngram\": \"11,000 athletes\", \"from\": 190, \"to\": 205}, {\"ngram\": \"42 Olympic disciplines\", \"from\": 222, \"to\": 244}, {\"ngram\": \"(July\", \"from\": 280, \"to\": 285}, {\"ngram\": \"the organisers\", \"from\": 316, \"to\": 330}, {\"ngram\": \"an opening ceremony\", \"from\": 334, \"to\": 353}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those who may have witnessed the ceremony (or saw the reports on same) would have had mixed views on the explicit or implicit messaging included and possibly how the messaging ties in with the event itself.\", \"from\": 399, \"to\": 605, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 428, \"to\": 440}, {\"ngram\": \"the reports\", \"from\": 449, \"to\": 460}, {\"ngram\": \"mixed views\", \"from\": 485, \"to\": 496}, {\"ngram\": \"the explicit or implicit messaging\", \"from\": 500, \"to\": 534}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 588, \"to\": 597}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The aspect of the ceremony that got the most rise was the segment that featured drag performers seated behind a long banquet table, which many interpreted to be a vile depiction ofLast Supper.\", \"from\": 606, \"to\": 798, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The aspect\", \"from\": 606, \"to\": 616}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 620, \"to\": 632}, {\"ngram\": \"the most rise\", \"from\": 642, \"to\": 655}, {\"ngram\": \"the segment\", \"from\": 660, \"to\": 671}, {\"ngram\": \"drag performers\", \"from\": 686, \"to\": 701}, {\"ngram\": \"a long banquet table\", \"from\": 716, \"to\": 736}, {\"ngram\": \"a vile depiction\", \"from\": 767, \"to\": 783}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony's artistic director, Thomas Jolly, has repeatedly stated that he wasn't inspired by Leonardo da Vinci's famous painting showing Jesus Christ and his apostles, but those who had seen it from that angle are unable to unsee.\", \"from\": 799, \"to\": 1033, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 833, \"end\": 839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.7824692798053021, \"rank\": 0.27791824931708986, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\"}, {\"begin\": 896, \"end\": 913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1734253843551007e-25, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 940, \"end\": 952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999995071167482, \"rank\": 4.928838519536705e-07, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The ceremony's artistic director\", \"from\": 799, \"to\": 831}, {\"ngram\": \"his apostles\", \"from\": 957, \"to\": 969}, {\"ngram\": \"that angle\", \"from\": 1002, \"to\": 1012}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many debates were ignited and the backlash has been far and wide, with some referring to the depiction as \\\"pagan and satanic\\\".\", \"from\": 1034, \"to\": 1160, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Many debates\", \"from\": 1034, \"to\": 1046}, {\"ngram\": \"the backlash\", \"from\": 1064, \"to\": 1076}, {\"ngram\": \"the depiction\", \"from\": 1123, \"to\": 1136}, {\"ngram\": \"pagan\", \"from\": 1141, \"to\": 1146}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympics organisers have since apologised to anyone who was offended by the display, but insist it was not based on any religious template.\", \"from\": 1161, \"to\": 1300, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympics organisers\", \"from\": 1161, \"to\": 1180}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 1206, \"to\": 1212}, {\"ngram\": \"the display\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1244}, {\"ngram\": \"any religious template\", \"from\": 1277, \"to\": 1299}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the first time in the history of the Olympic Games the opening ceremony did not take place in a stadium but was held along the city's main artery, the Seine river.\", \"from\": 1302, \"to\": 1469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1457, \"end\": 1462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.999999999920874, \"rank\": 7.53853241639812e-11, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1320}, {\"ngram\": \"the history\", \"from\": 1324, \"to\": 1335}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1339, \"to\": 1356}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1357, \"to\": 1377}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 1391, \"to\": 1396}, {\"ngram\": \"a stadium\", \"from\": 1400, \"to\": 1409}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's main artery\", \"from\": 1429, \"to\": 1451}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The traditional colourful parade of athletes took place in nearly 100 boats, along six kilometres of the Seine, passing the most iconic Parisian landmarks, and featured eclectic performances and musical presentations along the way.\", \"from\": 1470, \"to\": 1701, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1575, \"end\": 1580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.999999999920874, \"rank\": 7.53853241639812e-11, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The traditional colourful parade\", \"from\": 1470, \"to\": 1502}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1506, \"to\": 1514}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 1520, \"to\": 1525}, {\"ngram\": \"nearly 100 boats\", \"from\": 1529, \"to\": 1545}, {\"ngram\": \"six kilometres\", \"from\": 1553, \"to\": 1567}, {\"ngram\": \"the most iconic Parisian landmarks\", \"from\": 1590, \"to\": 1624}, {\"ngram\": \"featured eclectic performances\", \"from\": 1630, \"to\": 1660}, {\"ngram\": \"musical presentations\", \"from\": 1665, \"to\": 1686}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 1693, \"to\": 1700}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The rain-affected outdoor concept was reportedly the largest Olympic Opening Ceremony in terms of audience and geographical coverage.\", \"from\": 1702, \"to\": 1835, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The rain-affected outdoor concept\", \"from\": 1702, \"to\": 1735}, {\"ngram\": \"the largest Olympic Opening Ceremony\", \"from\": 1751, \"to\": 1787}, {\"ngram\": \"terms\", \"from\": 1791, \"to\": 1796}, {\"ngram\": \"audience and geographical coverage\", \"from\": 1800, \"to\": 1834}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately, amidst the background of ongoing military conflicts (Russia vs Ukraine and Israel vs Palestine), protests played out in the streets of Paris and a couple of contestants bypassed the usual courteous handshake, extending the political tension from the battlefield into the competitive athletic arena.\", \"from\": 1837, \"to\": 2150, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1905, \"end\": 1911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.8587572396712689, \"rank\": 0.16446810542831788, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 1915, \"end\": 1922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999995508043057, \"rank\": 2.919543169525846e-07, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 1927, \"end\": 1933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 6.081792755106991e-13, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}, {\"begin\": 1937, \"end\": 1946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\", \"score\": 0.999998901670245, \"rank\": 1.0978036514237684e-06, \"text\": \"Palestine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\"}, {\"begin\": 1987, \"end\": 1992, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.159691326143098e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the background\", \"from\": 1859, \"to\": 1873}, {\"ngram\": \"ongoing military conflicts\", \"from\": 1877, \"to\": 1903}, {\"ngram\": \"protests\", \"from\": 1949, \"to\": 1957}, {\"ngram\": \"the streets\", \"from\": 1972, \"to\": 1983}, {\"ngram\": \"a couple\", \"from\": 1997, \"to\": 2005}, {\"ngram\": \"contestants\", \"from\": 2009, \"to\": 2020}, {\"ngram\": \"the usual courteous handshake\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2059}, {\"ngram\": \"the political tension\", \"from\": 2071, \"to\": 2092}, {\"ngram\": \"the battlefield\", \"from\": 2098, \"to\": 2113}, {\"ngram\": \"the competitive athletic arena\", \"from\": 2119, \"to\": 2149}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And among the many pitfalls plaguing Paris 2024 is the scourge of the now -viral racist video clip, posted by the Argentinian football team following their COPA victory in mid-July, which continues to haunt them into the Olympics, plus dangerous levels of pollution in the Seine that resulted in the postponement of the men's individual triathlon event earlier this week.\", \"from\": 2151, \"to\": 2522, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2188, \"end\": 2198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.043453413896322e-33, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2265, \"end\": 2276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentines\", \"score\": 0.929797687054474, \"rank\": 0.05113342306860362, \"text\": \"Argentinian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentines\"}, {\"begin\": 2424, \"end\": 2429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.999999999920874, \"rank\": 7.538532416