n recent times there have been controversies over their inclusion, especially transgender women who transitioned from being men after puberty.\", \"from\": 3107, \"to\": 3333, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"transgender athletes\", \"from\": 3119, \"to\": 3139}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3172, \"to\": 3184}, {\"ngram\": \"recent times\", \"from\": 3193, \"to\": 3205}, {\"ngram\": \"controversies\", \"from\": 3222, \"to\": 3235}, {\"ngram\": \"their inclusion\", \"from\": 3241, \"to\": 3256}, {\"ngram\": \"especially transgender women\", \"from\": 3258, \"to\": 3286}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 3315, \"to\": 3318}, {\"ngram\": \"puberty\", \"from\": 3325, \"to\": 3332}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes such as American runner Nikki Hiltz and Canadian footballer Quinn, both of whom identify as transgender and non-binary, are competing in Paris.\", \"from\": 3334, \"to\": 3486, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3351, \"end\": 3359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999998435669, \"rank\": 1.5039406747195484e-10, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3367, \"end\": 3378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikki_Hiltz\", \"score\": 0.9999994965738909, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nikki Hiltz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikki_Hiltz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikki_Hiltz\"}, {\"begin\": 3383, \"end\": 3391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9821109896026334, \"rank\": 0.018214856044213093, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 3403, \"end\": 3408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quinn_Fabray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.972889189816394e-14, \"text\": \"Quinn\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quinn_Fabray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quinn_Fabray\"}, {\"begin\": 3480, \"end\": 3485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.159691326143098e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Athletes\", \"from\": 3334, \"to\": 3342}, {\"ngram\": \"transgender\", \"from\": 3435, \"to\": 3446}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both were born women and are competing as women but have reportedly suspended their testosterone treatment to ensure their levels do not surpass the allowed limit.\", \"from\": 3487, \"to\": 3650, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 3502, \"to\": 3507}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 3529, \"to\": 3534}, {\"ngram\": \"their testosterone treatment\", \"from\": 3565, \"to\": 3593}, {\"ngram\": \"their levels\", \"from\": 3604, \"to\": 3616}, {\"ngram\": \"the allowed limit\", \"from\": 3632, \"to\": 3649}]}, {\"sentence\": \"American swimmer Lia Thomas, on the other hand, is not allowed to compete in the Olympics after losing a legal battle last month against World Aquatics in a bid to be able to compete at Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 3652, \"to\": 3849, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3652, \"end\": 3660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999998435669, \"rank\": 1.5039406747195484e-10, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3669, \"end\": 3679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lia_Thomas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lia Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q1084340