e_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999989884941556, \"rank\": 1.0115067505402356e-06, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"born male\", \"from\": 3858, \"to\": 3867}, {\"ngram\": \"prominence\", \"from\": 3883, \"to\": 3893}, {\"ngram\": \"the first transgender athlete\", \"from\": 3909, \"to\": 3938}, {\"ngram\": \"biological women\", \"from\": 4068, \"to\": 4084}, {\"ngram\": \"international events\", \"from\": 4088, \"to\": 4108}, {\"ngram\": \"a change\", \"from\": 4119, \"to\": 4127}, {\"ngram\": \"regulations\", \"from\": 4131, \"to\": 4142}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Transgender males have a distinctly unfair advantage over biological women due to superior physical strength and higher testosterone levels.\", \"from\": 4145, \"to\": 4285, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Transgender males\", \"from\": 4145, \"to\": 4162}, {\"ngram\": \"a distinctly unfair advantage\", \"from\": 4168, \"to\": 4197}, {\"ngram\": \"biological women\", \"from\": 4203, \"to\": 4219}, {\"ngram\": \"superior physical strength\", \"from\": 4227, \"to\": 4253}, {\"ngram\": \"higher testosterone levels\", \"from\": 4258, \"to\": 4284}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is ruthlessly exacerbated in sports like boxing in which this advantage can lead to significant injuries, both immediate and long term.\", \"from\": 4286, \"to\": 4426, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 4320, \"to\": 4326}, {\"ngram\": \"this advantage\", \"from\": 4348, \"to\": 4362}, {\"ngram\": \"significant injuries\", \"from\": 4375, \"to\": 4395}, {\"ngram\": \"both immediate and long term\", \"from\": 4397, \"to\": 4425}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is the first Olympics in which the ratio of women to men is equal, and having this level of inequality is not only dangerous but is also bordering on criminal activity, thereby unsafely pushing inclusivity into overreach.\", \"from\": 4427, \"to\": 4653, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first Olympics\", \"from\": 4435, \"to\": 4453}, {\"ngram\": \"the ratio\", \"from\": 4463, \"to\": 4472}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 4476, \"to\": 4481}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 4485, \"to\": 4488}, {\"ngram\": \"this level\", \"from\": 4510, \"to\": 4520}, {\"ngram\": \"inequality\", \"from\": 4524, \"to\": 4534}, {\"ngram\": \"criminal activity\", \"from\": 4582, \"to\": 4599}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusivity\", \"from\": 4626, \"to\": 4637}, {\"ngram\": \"overreach\", \"from\": 4643, \"to\": 4652}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On a more positive note, the Jamaican track and field contingent begin their quest today in Paris, with hopes held aloft by Jamaicans at home and abroad.\", \"from\": 4655, \"to\": 4808, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4684, \"end\": 4692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9795001412042925, \"rank\": 0.020928898252794502, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}, {\"begin\": 4747, \"end\": 4752, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.159691326143098e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4779, \"end\": 4788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.588857007219838e-17, \"text\": \"Jamaicans\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a more positive note\", \"from\": 4658, \"to\": 4678}, {\"ngram\": \"their quest\", \"from\": 4726, \"to\": 4737}, {\"ngram\": \"hopes\", \"from\": 4759, \"to\